I live in metro Detroit.

From silly to science, Emmy Award winner Alan Teitel and his UltraSlo Studio create compelling slow motion video images for online entertainment and education. Slow motion videos from the Ultraslo stock video library are used in documentaries commercials and scientific research world wide. Slow motion videos from UltraSlo have been viewed oner a quarter of a billion times on all the sites that love to stream  slow motion videos around the world

Alan has a unique outlook and viewing perspective based on his twenty-five years of slow motion and 3d work which allow him to see the world at a much different speed. Alan is a director, cinematographer and producer of national commercials, documentaries, and dramatic scenes. 

Alan won two Emmy's for Cinematography and Technical Achievement. Alan has been nominated six times for his outstanding work on broadcast television

description:
THANKS FOR STOPPING BY!

FIRST OFF - I HAVE A NEW CHANNEL SPECIFICALLY JUST FOR MY FILMING WORK.  @two08Raw

I’m just a semi normal fella that loves to spend time outside and usually films ANYTHING with a motor. I’m the filming philanthropist.  I like making other people look good. 

This channel is a hodgepodge of everything. It can be either a behind the lens video, a review or just me living the best life I can in the short amount of time I’m here.  If it involves a motor of some type, I’m in!

I started this channel when the tube was new back in the day (Sep 27, 2006). 

In January of 2023 I made a promise to myself that I would post a new (long form) video every week(ish)for as long as possible. 

It’s a pretty informal channel, more of a “VLOG” style. Kind rough around the edges and raw. No fancy lighting or editing. 

Poke that thumbs up on any videos that tickles your fancy. 

Thanks for checking out the channel!

My name's Mike, I'm a sponsored skater for Shell Shock Skateboards and a mechanical engineering graduate from stony brook university

I'm the only skater on this channel, everything you see was made and done by myself
Engineering and life stuff happens a lot with me, so I try to skate when I can! (which ends up being once or twice a week unfortunately).  So if you see that I haven't uploaded anything in a while, it's because of that.  So yeah, there could be times when my uploading rate becomes pretty slow, but no worries.  My main goal for this channel is to try to make trick tips for every trick I know, so I'll probably be on youtube uploading videos for quite some time, for sure haha

description:
I'm Daniel Soulbuilt and I design and make cool things. Some of them turn into awesome products. Subscribe for all things Engineerable. SOUL BUILT is my brand for the cool things that I invent, make and sell:

KRVR Knives - I and my small team of craftsmen & craftswomen make custom chef knives with damascus blades and wicked cool handles. You'll find videos of individual knives that we have made, and I also post instructional videos to document the knife-making process and share our knowledge with you.

SoulBuilt makes EDC accessories like the MARKSMITH Titanium Bolt Action permanent marker.

I do unboxing and reviews of products that I buy for use by myself or at the ENGINEERABLE + SOUL BUILT shop. I spend a lot of time researching these products beforehand, so I already know that they are not shit when I review them.

I post a lot of DIY videos because I think it's important to document what we do as humans so that we can learn from each other and constantly improve.

Are you ready to unlock your full potential in martial arts tricking, parkour, physical wellness, and obstacle-based fitness? You've just landed in the right place!

I'm Kyle Mendoza, and I'm on a mission to help YOU become a movement maestro. With years of experience in martial arts tricking, parkour, and mastering the art of mobility, I'm here to be your guide on this epic journey. My passion is sharing in-depth tutorials, step-by-step breakdowns, and inspirational challenges. I'm here to break down the barriers that hold you back and empower you with the knowledge you need to thrive in the world of movement.

Our channel is for high-energy kids who love to leap off everything, misfit teens seeking an outlet for mental and physical expression, and adults who want to maintain a mobile and functional body. If you're looking for a positive, supportive, and inspiring community, you're family here.

I'm Roger from Minneapolis, Minnesota, and this is one of 4 channels, separated for each of my interests.

- Roger Lawrence (attempt at a stage name from my move to California in 2014) for my acting and editing projects

description:
“Inspiring images. Since 1917.” ARRI is a global player within the motion picture industry, employing around 1,200 staff worldwide. 
Named after its founders August Arnold and Robert Richter, ARRI was established in Munich, Germany, where the headquarters is still located today. Subsidiaries are in Europe, North and South America, Asia, and Australia. 
The ARRI Group consists of the business units Camera Systems, Lighting, and Rental, all dedicated to connecting creativity and future technologies for moving images. ARRI is a leading designer and manufacturer of camera and lighting systems as well as system solutions for the film, broadcast, and media industries, with a worldwide distribution and service network. The portfolio includes digital cameras, lenses, camera accessories, archive technologies, lamp heads, and lighting accessories. Along with offering exclusive technologies, ARRI Rental’s first-class services and equipment provide camera, lighting, and grip packages.

Witajcie na moim kanale CODApl.

Ten kanał to miejsce, w którym znajdziecie zarówno nagrywki na rzecz mojego Moto Vloga, jak również nagrania z wyścigów samochodowych, pokazów lotniczy... i nie tylko. Będę tu zamieszczać wszystkie ciekawe rzeczy, które uda mi się sfilmować a jednocześnie uznam, że są one warte pokazania. Głównie jednak kanał będzie skupiać się wokół szeroko pojętej motoryzacji i tego co dostarcza adrenaliny i pozostaje w moim zasięgu.

Duży nacisk kładę na jakość nagrań, zarówno pod kątem obrazu jak i dźwięku dlatego polecam oglądać w jakości HD.

Zachęcam do subskrypcji oraz śledzenia moich profili na portalach społecznościowych.

description:
The "Jack of all trades and master of some", Ian directs, produces, edits, creates visual effects, and gets his hands on the camera including certified jib user. Ian Morris was born and raised in the City of Sin, Las Vegas. He is a graduate of San Diego State's Television, Film and New Media program after serving seven years in the United States Navy.
His previous works are currently traveling the film festival circuit. "Fatal Fetish" was featured at the Latino Film Festival in March 2012 and also featured at CineVegas in June 2012. One of Ian's recent accomplishment is a Student Emmy nomination for directing the newscast production "Aztec News" at San Diego State University where he took on the tedious task of adopting brand new equipment in two days and creating a cutting-edge newcast.

description:
Jarno was a world champion wingsuit pilot skydiver and base jumper with more than 20 years of experience.

Specialized in wingsuit acrobatics, aerial cinematography and stunts for TV and film, and coaching, he is one of the highest ranking professionals in the sport. His efforts led the creation of coaching and training techniques for indoor wingsuit flying.

In the competitive world Jarno has a wide range of experience and 1st place podium results and world champion titles, spanning all disciplines of Wingsuit Skydiving, Indoor Wingsuit Flying and Wingsuit BASE jumping.

Jarno tragically died during a wingsuit / basejump accident january 4th 2023 in Switserland. His loving family wishes to honor him by keeping this channel up.
